      <h4><strong>Campus Placement - Procedure and Information:</strong> 
For an IT and Engineering graduates, Infosys is one of the most sought after companies to work. Infosys offers excellent careers opportunities and has world class training centres which are very appealing to a fresh graduate. It is one of the most awaited companies and every year many students prepare in advance to attend the campus interview. Students are offered entry level job at engineering, as well as management level.

It has been seen that like every company Infosys too has an eligibility criteria. The candidate should at least score first class in SSC and HSC exams and should have an aggregate of 68% in B- Tech. Also, he/she should not have any active backlog. 

It has been always observed that, Infosys has a well-structured selection procedure of campus recruitment. Infosys has two rounds of interview. The first round is a written test. The written test is divided in two sections; one is the aptitude test and the other is the verbal ability test. There is a limited time give to solve the written test. There are no negative marking in both the sections.
